Even though process_with_pandas might detect multiple retailers in the CSV, the function only uploads data for the retailer specified in the event. This prevents "fan-out" -- where one Lambda invocation accidentally overwrites data for other retailers that have their own dedicated invocations. If the event retailer isn't in the output, it fails.

