In essence, process_file takes a raw vendor CSV from S3, validates it, transforms it to standard format, ensures only the correct retailer's data is processed, uploads it to the client's VIP bucket, and then runs health checks (drift detection) on the data quality -- all while logging everything to Datadog and Slack.
